        "content": "<p>The category of (affine) Lagrangian relations over a field gives a semantics for certain classes of electrical circuits, and even stabilizer circuits, given the appropriate field.</p>\n<p>There is a cateogry of isotropic relations, where the morphisms are isotropic subspaces of the product space of the domain and codomain, and whose composition is the relational one.</p>\n<p>Does anyone know if there are interesting things in electrical circuits or quantum theory which are be modelled by (co)isotropic subspaces, but not Lagrangian subspaces, in general?</p>",
        "id": 240703585,
        "sender_full_name": "Cole Comfort",
        "timestamp": 1622296485
    },
    {
